WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.846 --> 00:00:16.892
As the first century of the
Targaryen dynasty came to a close.

2
00:00:17.351 --> 00:00:22.189
the health of the old king.
jaehaerys. was failing.

3
00:00:24.399 --> 00:00:28.403
In those days. house Targaryen
stood at the height of its strength.

4
00:00:29.071 --> 00:00:32.074
with ten adult dragons under its yoke.

5
00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:35.244
No power in the world
could stand against it.

6
00:00:36.828 --> 00:00:41.375
King jaehaerys reigned over nearly
60 years of peace and prosperity.

7
00:00:41.458 --> 00:00:46.838
But tragedy had claimed both his sons.
leaving his succession in doubt.

8
00:00:47.464 --> 00:00:54.221
So. in the year 101. the old king called
a great council to choose an heir.

9
00:00:55.722 --> 00:00:58.725
Over a thousand lords made
the journey to harrenhal.

10
00:01:00.227 --> 00:01:06.358
Fourteen succession claims were heard.
but only two were truly considered.

11
00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:11.238
Princess rhaenys Targaryen.
the king's eldest descendant.

12
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:14.950
and her younger cousin.
prince viserys Targaryen.

13
00:01:15.033 --> 00:01:17.869
the king's eldest male descendant.

14
00:01:23.834 --> 00:01:28.922
It is declared
by all lords Paramount

15
00:01:29.006 --> 00:01:32.593
and lords vassal of the seven kingdoms.

16
00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:36.972
that prince viserys Targaryen...

17
00:01:37.055 --> 00:01:40.559
Be made prince of dragonstone.

18
00:01:40.642 --> 00:01:42.853
Rhaenys. a woman.

19
00:01:42.936 --> 00:01:45.939
would not inherit the iron throne.

20
00:01:48.483 --> 00:01:50.902
The lords instead chose viserys.

21
00:01:52.446 --> 00:01:53.655
my father.

22
00:01:57.159 --> 00:01:59.161
Jaehaerys called the great council

23
00:01:59.244 --> 00:02:02.956
to prevent a war being
fought over his succession.

24
00:02:03.040 --> 00:02:05.042
For he knew the cold truth.

25
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:07.419
The only thing that could tear down

26
00:02:07.502 --> 00:02:10.172
the house of the dragon.

27
00:02:10.255 --> 00:02:11.465
was itself.

28
00:04:03.368 --> 00:04:06.037
Dohaeras. syrax!

29
00:04:09.458 --> 00:04:10.459
Umbas.

30
00:04:12.335 --> 00:04:13.336
Rybas!

31
00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:26.993
Welcome back. Princess.

32
00:04:27.017 --> 00:04:28.560
I trust your ride was pleasant.

33
00:04:28.643 --> 00:04:30.729
Try not to look too relieved. ser.

34
00:04:30.812 --> 00:04:31.938
I am relieved.

35
00:04:32.022 --> 00:04:35.317
Every time that golden beast
brings you back unspoiled.

36
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:37.319
it saves my head from a spike.

37
00:04:38.403 --> 00:04:40.197
Syrax is growing quickly.

38
00:04:40.280 --> 00:04:42.407
She'll soon be as large as caraxes.

39
00:04:42.491 --> 00:04:44.367
That's almost large enough
to saddle two.

40
00:04:44.451 --> 00:04:47.454
I believe I'm quite content
as a spectator. thank you.

41
00:04:50.457 --> 00:04:52.417
Dohaeras.

42
00:04:54.085 --> 00:04:55.086
Naejot!

43
00:06:21.715 --> 00:06:24.259
Ah. rhaenyra.

44
00:06:26.595 --> 00:06:29.764
You know I don't like you to go flying
while I'm in this condition.

45
00:06:29.848 --> 00:06:32.248
You don't like me to go flying
while you're in any condition.

46
00:06:34.269 --> 00:06:37.230
- Your grace.
- Good morrow. alicent.

47
00:06:37.314 --> 00:06:38.607
Did you sleep?

48
00:06:38.690 --> 00:06:40.734
- I slept.
- How long?

49
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.945
I don't need mothering. rhaenyra.

50
00:06:44.029 --> 00:06:46.281
Well. here you are.
surrounded by attendants.

51
00:06:46.364 --> 00:06:48.199
all focused on the babe.

52
00:06:48.783 --> 00:06:50.619
Someone has to attend to you.

53
00:06:52.287 --> 00:06:56.374
You will lie in this bed
soon enough. rhaenyra.

54
00:06:56.458 --> 00:07:00.003
This discomfort
is how we serve the realm.

55
00:07:00.086 --> 00:07:03.381
I'd rather serve as a knight
and ride to battle and glory.

56
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:08.637
We have royal wombs. you and I.

57
00:07:10.305 --> 00:07:12.390
The childbed is our battlefield.

58
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.395
We must learn to face it
with a stiff lip.

59
00:07:18.772 --> 00:07:20.690
Now take a bath.

60
00:07:20.774 --> 00:07:22.776
You stink of dragon.

61
00:07:24.903 --> 00:07:28.114
So. I said to him. "well. I believe you
might be looking up the wrong end."

62
00:07:32.160 --> 00:07:33.662
My lords.

63
00:07:33.745 --> 00:07:35.664
The growing alliance
among the free cities

64
00:07:35.747 --> 00:07:38.833
has taken to styling
itself "the triarchy."

65
00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:40.919
They have massed on bloodstone

66
00:07:41.002 --> 00:07:44.339
and are presently ridding the stepstones
of its pirate infestation.

67
00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:46.967
Well. that sounds suspiciously
like good news. lord corlys.

68
00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:49.135
A man called craghas drahar

69
00:07:49.219 --> 00:07:52.222
has styled himself the prince-admiral
of this triarchy.

70
00:07:53.556 --> 00:07:55.767
They call him "the crabfeeder"

71
00:07:55.850 --> 00:07:58.770
due to his inventive methods
of punishing his enemies.

72
00:07:58.853 --> 00:08:01.272
And are we meant to weep
for dead pirates?

73
00:08:02.148 --> 00:08:04.192
- No. your grace.
- Rhaenyra. you're late.

74
00:08:04.818 --> 00:08:06.319
King's cupbearer must not be late.

75
00:08:06.403 --> 00:08:09.447
- Leaves people wanting for cups.
- I was visiting mother.

76
00:08:11.741 --> 00:08:12.951
On dragonback?

77
00:08:13.576 --> 00:08:16.162
Uh. your grace.
at prince daemon's urging.

78
00:08:16.246 --> 00:08:18.790
the crown has invested
significant capital

79
00:08:18.873 --> 00:08:22.293
in the re-training and re-equipping
of his city watch.

80
00:08:22.377 --> 00:08:26.673
I thought you might urge your brother
to fill his seat on the council

81
00:08:26.756 --> 00:08:29.551
and provide an assessment
of his progress

82
00:08:29.634 --> 00:08:31.678
as commander of the watch.

83
00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:34.305
Do you think daemon
is distracted by his present tasks?

84
00:08:34.389 --> 00:08:36.599
And that his thoughts
and energies are occupied?

85
00:08:36.683 --> 00:08:39.644
Well. one would hope so.
considering the associated costs.

86
00:08:39.728 --> 00:08:42.272
Then let us all consider
your gold well-invested. lord beesbury.

87
00:08:43.189 --> 00:08:46.234
I would urge that you not allow
this triarchy much latitude

88
00:08:46.317 --> 00:08:48.486
in the stepstones. your grace.

89
00:08:48.570 --> 00:08:51.656
If those shipping lanes should fall.
it will beggar our ports.

90
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:54.367
The crown has heard
your report. lord corlys.

91
00:08:54.451 --> 00:08:57.078
and takes it under advisement.

92
00:09:01.833 --> 00:09:05.045
Shall we discuss the heir's tournament.
your grace?

93
00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:08.298
I would be delighted.

94
00:09:08.381 --> 00:09:10.425
Will the maesters' name day
prediction hold. mellos?

95
00:09:10.508 --> 00:09:14.012
You must understand that these things
are mere estimations. my king.

96
00:09:14.095 --> 00:09:17.182
but we have all been
poring over the moon charts.

97
00:09:17.265 --> 00:09:21.352
and we feel that our forecast
is as accurate as it can be.

98
00:09:21.436 --> 00:09:24.230
The cost
of the tournament is not negligible.

99
00:09:24.314 --> 00:09:28.193
Perhaps we might delay
until the child is in hand?

100
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:30.963
Most of the lords
and knights are certainly on their way

101
00:09:30.987 --> 00:09:32.987
to king's landing already.
To turn them back now...

102
00:09:33.031 --> 00:09:35.009
The tourney will take
the better part of a week.

103
00:09:35.033 --> 00:09:37.827
Before the games are over.
my son will be born.

104
00:09:37.911 --> 00:09:39.537
and the whole realm will celebrate.

105
00:09:39.621 --> 00:09:42.791
We have no way of predicting
the sex of the child.

106
00:09:42.874 --> 00:09:45.627
Of course. no maester's capable
of rendering an opinion

107
00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:47.128
free of conditions. are they now?

108
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:50.256
There's a boy in the queen's belly.

109
00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:52.092
I know it.

110
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:55.804
And my heir will soon
put all of this damnable

111
00:09:55.887 --> 00:09:57.889
hand-wringing to rest himself.

112
00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:03.204
He passed through
the red keep's gates at first light.

113
00:10:03.228 --> 00:10:05.188
Does my father know he's here?

114
00:10:05.271 --> 00:10:06.648
- No.
- Good.

115
00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:16.366
Gods be good.

116
00:10:16.908 --> 00:10:18.535
It's all right. ser.

117
00:10:40.348 --> 00:10:41.391
Aye.

118
00:11:11.921 --> 00:11:13.464
I bought you something.

119
00:11:18.970 --> 00:11:20.388
Do you know what it is?

120
00:11:21.639 --> 00:11:23.266
It's valyrian steel.

121
00:11:24.434 --> 00:11:26.060
Like dark sister.

122
00:11:29.939 --> 00:11:31.149
Turn around.

123
00:11:45.872 --> 00:11:46.873
Now.

124
00:11:48.249 --> 00:11:51.669
you and I both own a small piece
of our ancestry.

125
00:12:02.096 --> 00:12:03.240
Did you read it?

126
00:12:03.264 --> 00:12:04.766
Of course. I read it.

127
00:12:04.849 --> 00:12:07.143
When Princess nymeria
arrived in dorne.

128
00:12:07.227 --> 00:12:09.062
who did she take to husband?

129
00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:10.521
A man.

130
00:12:10.605 --> 00:12:12.106
What was his name?

131
00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:13.942
Lord something.

132
00:12:14.025 --> 00:12:15.628
If you answer with
"lord something."

133
00:12:15.652 --> 00:12:17.403
septa Marlow will be furious.

134
00:12:17.487 --> 00:12:19.489
She's funny when she's furious.

135
00:12:22.659 --> 00:12:25.161
You're always like this
when you're worried.

136
00:12:25.245 --> 00:12:26.621
Like what?

137
00:12:26.704 --> 00:12:28.164
Disagreeable.

138
00:12:32.252 --> 00:12:34.504
You're worried your father
is about to overshadow you

139
00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:35.964
with a son.

140
00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:37.924
I only worry for my mother.

141
00:12:38.967 --> 00:12:41.386
I hope for my father that he gets a son.

142
00:12:42.095 --> 00:12:44.639
As long as I can recall.
it's all he's wanted.

143
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:47.642
You want him to have a son?

144
00:12:47.725 --> 00:12:49.519
I want to fly with you on dragonback.

145
00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:51.354
see the great wonders
across the narrow sea.

146
00:12:51.437 --> 00:12:52.689
and eat only cake.

147
00:12:52.772 --> 00:12:55.275
- I'm being serious.
- I neverjest about cake.

148
00:12:55.733 --> 00:12:57.485
You aren't worried about your position?

149
00:12:57.568 --> 00:13:00.238
I like this position.
It's quite comfortable.

150
00:13:04.075 --> 00:13:07.704
- Where are you going?
- Home. The hour has grown late.

151
00:13:08.621 --> 00:13:10.623
Princess nymeria led her rhoynar

152
00:13:10.707 --> 00:13:12.792
across the narrow sea on 10.000 ships

153
00:13:12.875 --> 00:13:14.877
to flee their valyrian pursuers.

154
00:13:14.961 --> 00:13:18.047
She took lord mors martell
of dorne to husband

155
00:13:18.131 --> 00:13:19.966
and burned her own fleet off sunspear

156
00:13:20.049 --> 00:13:22.093
to show her people
that they were finished running.

157
00:13:24.345 --> 00:13:26.764
- What are you doing?
- So you remember.

158
00:13:27.557 --> 00:13:30.601
- If the septa sees this book. then...
- Fuck the septa.

159
00:13:30.685 --> 00:13:32.186
Rhaenyra!

160
00:13:44.866 --> 00:13:46.367
Is it healing?

161
00:13:46.451 --> 00:13:49.329
It has grown slightly.
your grace.

162
00:13:51.331 --> 00:13:53.583
Can you say yet what it is?

163
00:13:53.666 --> 00:13:55.835
We've sent inquiries to the citadel.

164
00:13:55.918 --> 00:13:58.046
They are searching
the texts for similar cases.

165
00:13:58.129 --> 00:14:00.381
It's a small cut
from sitting the throne.

166
00:14:00.465 --> 00:14:01.466
It's nothing.

167
00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:06.262
The king has been under heavy stresses
preparing for the birth.

168
00:14:07.263 --> 00:14:11.851
Bad humors of the mind
can adversely affect the body.

169
00:14:11.934 --> 00:14:15.146
Whatever it is.
it needs to be kept quiet.

170
00:14:18.649 --> 00:14:20.169
We should leech it again.
maester.

171
00:14:20.193 --> 00:14:22.820
It's a wound that refuses to heal.
grand maester.

172
00:14:24.238 --> 00:14:25.948
Might I suggest cauterization?

173
00:14:26.032 --> 00:14:29.702
Cauterization would be a wise
course of treatment. your grace.

174
00:14:30.328 --> 00:14:32.330
- It will be painful.
- Fine.

175
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:34.832
Fine.

176
00:14:47.762 --> 00:14:50.240
You spend more time
in that bath than I do on the throne.

177
00:14:51.349 --> 00:14:54.727
This is the only place
I can find comfort these days.

178
00:14:57.146 --> 00:14:58.648
It's tepid.

179
00:14:58.731 --> 00:15:01.234
It's as warm as the maesters will allow.

180
00:15:01.317 --> 00:15:03.736
- Don't they know dragons prefer heat?
- Hmm.

181
00:15:04.946 --> 00:15:07.865
After this miserable pregnancy.

182
00:15:07.949 --> 00:15:11.285
I wouldn't be surprised
if I hatched an actual dragon.

183
00:15:11.369 --> 00:15:13.830
Then he will be loved
and cherished.

184
00:15:14.831 --> 00:15:17.792
Rhaenyra has already declared
that she is to have a sister.

185
00:15:17.875 --> 00:15:19.293
Really?

186
00:15:19.377 --> 00:15:22.380
- She even named her.
- Dare I ask?

187
00:15:23.214 --> 00:15:24.924
Visenya.

188
00:15:25.007 --> 00:15:28.511
She chose a dragon's egg for the cradle
that she said reminded her of vhagar.

189
00:15:28.594 --> 00:15:30.138
Gods be good.

190
00:15:30.221 --> 00:15:32.640
This family already has its visenya.

191
00:15:34.600 --> 00:15:37.270
Has there been any word
from your dear brother?

192
00:15:37.353 --> 00:15:40.231
Not since I named him
commander of the city watch.

193
00:15:40.815 --> 00:15:43.234
I'm sure he will reemerge
for the tourney.

194
00:15:43.943 --> 00:15:46.446
He could never stay away from the lists.

195
00:15:46.529 --> 00:15:47.864
The tourney

196
00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:51.075
to celebrate the firstborn son
that we presently do not have.

197
00:15:52.452 --> 00:15:56.038
You do understand nothing
will cause the babe to grow a cock

198
00:15:56.122 --> 00:15:57.957
if it does not already possess one?

199
00:15:58.624 --> 00:16:00.001
This child is a boy. aemma.

200
00:16:01.294 --> 00:16:02.837
I'm certain of it.

201
00:16:03.379 --> 00:16:05.798
I've never been
more certain of anything.

202
00:16:09.594 --> 00:16:10.970
The dream.

203
00:16:11.971 --> 00:16:13.973
It was clearer than a memory.

204
00:16:16.225 --> 00:16:18.728
Our son was born wearing
aegon's iron crown.

205
00:16:20.897 --> 00:16:24.275
When I heard the sound
of thundering hooves.

206
00:16:24.358 --> 00:16:27.570
splintering shields. and ringing swords.

207
00:16:27.653 --> 00:16:30.656
and I placed our son
upon the iron throne

208
00:16:31.866 --> 00:16:34.327
as the bells of the grand sept tolled

209
00:16:34.410 --> 00:16:36.704
and all the dragons roared as one.

210
00:16:40.124 --> 00:16:41.542
Born wearing a crown?

211
00:16:42.335 --> 00:16:43.961
Gods spare me.

212
00:16:44.045 --> 00:16:46.506
birth is unpleasant enough as it is.

213
00:16:55.556 --> 00:16:59.101
This is the last time. viserys.

214
00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:03.773
I've lost one babe in the cradle.

215
00:17:03.856 --> 00:17:05.608
had two stillbirths. and two pregnancies

216
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.902
ended well before their term.

217
00:17:10.780 --> 00:17:13.491
That's five in twice as many years.

218
00:17:15.159 --> 00:17:18.037
I know it is my duty
to provide you an heir.

219
00:17:18.120 --> 00:17:21.749
and I'm sorry if I have
failed you in that. I am.

220
00:17:25.586 --> 00:17:28.589
But I've mourned
all the dead children I can.

221
00:17:49.652 --> 00:17:51.654
Commander on the floor!

222
00:17:58.327 --> 00:18:01.831
When I took command of the watch.
you were stray mongrels.

223
00:18:03.416 --> 00:18:05.710
starving and undisciplined.

224
00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:08.671
Now.

225
00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:11.299
you're a pack of hounds.

226
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:13.926
You're sated and honed for the hunt.

227
00:18:17.805 --> 00:18:20.641
My brother's city
has fallen into squalor.

228
00:18:21.934 --> 00:18:25.646
Crime of every breed
has been allowed to thrive.

229
00:18:27.440 --> 00:18:28.816
Nolongeh

230
00:18:28.899 --> 00:18:30.943
beginning tonight.
king's landing will learn

231
00:18:31.027 --> 00:18:32.862
to fear the color gold.

232
00:19:19.325 --> 00:19:20.660
Get up!

233
00:19:40.471 --> 00:19:41.681
Raper!

234
00:19:43.891 --> 00:19:46.977
No! No! No! No! No!

235
00:19:54.735 --> 00:19:56.404
Thief!

236
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:04.829
Murderer!

237
00:20:21.387 --> 00:20:24.724
It was an unprecedented
roundup of criminals of every ilk.

238
00:20:24.807 --> 00:20:26.892
Your brother made a public show of it.

239
00:20:26.976 --> 00:20:29.812
meting out
the summary judgments himself

240
00:20:29.895 --> 00:20:32.940
I'm told they needed a two-horse cart

241
00:20:33.023 --> 00:20:34.942
to haul away
the resulting dismemberments

242
00:20:35.025 --> 00:20:36.193
when it was done.

243
00:20:36.277 --> 00:20:38.237
Gods be good.

244
00:20:39.155 --> 00:20:40.948
The prince cannot
be allowed to act

245
00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:43.826
with this kind of unchecked impunity.

246
00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:48.038
- Brother.
- Daemon.

247
00:20:49.790 --> 00:20:52.793
Carry on. You were saying
something about my impunity.

248
00:20:55.296 --> 00:20:58.591
You are to explain your doings
with the city watch.

249
00:21:01.177 --> 00:21:04.263
Your new "gold cloaks" made quite
the impression last night. didn't they?

250
00:21:04.346 --> 00:21:05.598
Did they?

251
00:21:05.681 --> 00:21:08.934
The city watch is not a sword
to be wielded at your whim.

252
00:21:09.018 --> 00:21:11.020
They're an extension of the crown.

253
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:13.063
The watch was enforcing
the crown's laws.

254
00:21:13.147 --> 00:21:14.857
Wouldn't you agree. lord strong?

255
00:21:16.066 --> 00:21:17.526
My prince. I don't think...

256
00:21:17.610 --> 00:21:20.154
Making a public spectacle
of wanton brutality

257
00:21:20.237 --> 00:21:22.031
is hardly in line with our laws.

258
00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:23.699
Nobles from every corner of the realm

259
00:21:23.783 --> 00:21:25.701
are right now descending
upon king's landing

260
00:21:25.785 --> 00:21:27.328
for my brother's tourney.

261
00:21:27.411 --> 00:21:29.955
Do you want them
mugged. raped. murdered?

262
00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:32.708
You mightn't know this unless
you left the safety of the red keep.

263
00:21:32.792 --> 00:21:35.336
but much of king's landing
is seen by the smallfolk

264
00:21:35.419 --> 00:21:38.130
as lawless and terrifying.

265
00:21:40.424 --> 00:21:42.676
Our city should be safe
for all its people.

266
00:21:43.594 --> 00:21:44.595
I agree.

267
00:21:45.471 --> 00:21:49.266
I just hope you don't have to maim
half of my city to achieve this.

268
00:21:49.350 --> 00:21:50.768
Time will tell.

269
00:21:53.479 --> 00:21:57.775
We installed prince daemon
as commander to promote law and order.

270
00:21:57.858 --> 00:22:00.027
The criminal element
should fear the city watch.

271
00:22:00.110 --> 00:22:01.779
Thank you for your support. lord corlys.

272
00:22:01.862 --> 00:22:03.739
If only the prince
would show the same devotion

273
00:22:03.823 --> 00:22:06.617
to his lady wife as he does his work.
your grace.

274
00:22:06.700 --> 00:22:10.371
You've not been seen in the vale
or at runestone for quite some time.

275
00:22:10.454 --> 00:22:12.665
I think my bronze bitch
is happier for my absence.

276
00:22:12.748 --> 00:22:14.333
Lady rhea is your wife.

277
00:22:14.416 --> 00:22:16.836
a good and honorable lady of the vale.

278
00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:19.797
In the vale. men are said to fuck sheep
instead of women.

279
00:22:19.880 --> 00:22:22.341
I can assure you.
the sheep are prettier.

280
00:22:22.424 --> 00:22:23.425
Dear me.

281
00:22:23.509 --> 00:22:26.428
You made a vow before the seven
to honor your wife in marriage.

282
00:22:26.512 --> 00:22:28.931
Well. I'd gladly give lady rhea to you.
lord hightower.

283
00:22:29.014 --> 00:22:31.851
if you're in want
of a woman to warm your bed.

284
00:22:31.934 --> 00:22:34.144
Your own lady wife passed recently.

285
00:22:36.814 --> 00:22:38.440
Did she not?

286
00:22:38.524 --> 00:22:39.525
Otto.

287
00:22:42.945 --> 00:22:45.030
Perhaps you aren't ready
to move on just yet.

288
00:22:46.282 --> 00:22:48.617
You know how my brother
makes sport of provoking you.

289
00:22:49.535 --> 00:22:50.911
Must you indulge him?

290
00:22:55.249 --> 00:22:57.042
My apologies. your grace.

291
00:22:57.376 --> 00:23:00.337
This council has.
at great expense.

292
00:23:00.421 --> 00:23:03.048
bettered the city watch
to your exacting standards.

293
00:23:03.132 --> 00:23:06.010
Enforce my laws. but understand.

294
00:23:06.427 --> 00:23:09.805
any further performances
like last night's will be answered.

295
00:23:13.976 --> 00:23:15.269
Understood. your grace.

296
00:23:29.325 --> 00:23:31.911
King's landing has been in decline
since my grandmother passed.

297
00:23:32.912 --> 00:23:34.246
In the end.

298
00:23:35.039 --> 00:23:38.042
this new city watch
might be a good thing.

299
00:24:24.546 --> 00:24:26.548
What troubles you. my prince?

300
00:24:32.888 --> 00:24:34.890
I could bring in another.

301
00:24:35.349 --> 00:24:36.976
Perhaps a maiden.

302
00:24:38.143 --> 00:24:39.603
I have several.

303
00:24:41.563 --> 00:24:44.400
I could even arrange one
with silver hair.

304
00:24:50.614 --> 00:24:52.199
You are daemon Targaryen.

305
00:24:53.409 --> 00:24:56.412
Rider of caraxes.
Wielder of dark sister.

306
00:24:57.287 --> 00:24:59.206
The king cannot replace you.

307
00:25:12.428 --> 00:25:14.054
Be welcome!

308
00:25:14.888 --> 00:25:17.474
I know many of you have
traveled long leagues

309
00:25:17.558 --> 00:25:19.727
to be at these games.

310
00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:23.022
But I promise.
you will not be disappointed.

311
00:25:24.398 --> 00:25:27.484
When I look at
the fine knights in these lists.

312
00:25:27.568 --> 00:25:31.196
I see a group without equal
in our histories.

313
00:25:32.573 --> 00:25:37.661
And this great day
has been made more auspicious

314
00:25:37.745 --> 00:25:41.415
by the news
that I am happy to share:

315
00:25:42.541 --> 00:25:45.586
Queen aemma has begun her labors!

316
00:25:49.048 --> 00:25:52.468
May the luck of the seven
shine upon all combatants!

317
00:26:12.863 --> 00:26:13.906
Ah!

318
00:26:26.085 --> 00:26:27.336
A mystery knight?

319
00:26:27.419 --> 00:26:29.546
No. a Cole. of the stormlands.

320
00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:31.090
I've never heard of house Cole.

321
00:26:31.173 --> 00:26:33.884
Princess rhaenys Targaryen!

322
00:26:33.967 --> 00:26:36.011
I would humbly ask for the favor

323
00:26:36.095 --> 00:26:38.013
of "the queen who never was."

324
00:26:44.561 --> 00:26:46.081
Good fortune to you. cousin.

325
00:26:46.105 --> 00:26:48.482
I would gladly take it
if I thought I needed it.

326
00:26:54.988 --> 00:26:58.075
You could have
Baratheon's tongue for that.

327
00:26:58.158 --> 00:27:00.202
Tongues will not change the succession.

328
00:27:00.661 --> 00:27:02.037
Let them wag.

329
00:27:08.502 --> 00:27:11.880
Lord stokeworth's daughter
is promised to that young tarly squire.

330
00:27:11.964 --> 00:27:13.024
- Lord massey's son?
- Mmm-hmm.

331
00:27:13.048 --> 00:27:16.301
They're to be married
as soon as he wins his knighthood.

332
00:27:16.385 --> 00:27:17.511
Best get on with it.

333
00:27:19.054 --> 00:27:22.474
I heard that lady Elinor is hiding
a swollen belly beneath her dress.

334
00:27:45.414 --> 00:27:47.791
What do you know about
this ser criston Cole. ser harrold?

335
00:27:47.875 --> 00:27:49.751
I'm told ser criston
is common-born.

336
00:27:49.835 --> 00:27:51.378
son of lord dondarrion's steward.

337
00:27:51.461 --> 00:27:54.423
But other than that.
and the fact that he's just unhorsed

338
00:27:54.506 --> 00:27:56.466
both of the Baratheon lads.

339
00:27:56.550 --> 00:27:57.926
I really couldn't say.

340
00:28:16.612 --> 00:28:20.157
Prince daemon of house Targaryen.

341
00:28:20.240 --> 00:28:21.658
prince of the city.

342
00:28:21.742 --> 00:28:25.579
will now choose his first opponent!

343
00:29:03.075 --> 00:29:05.327
For his first challenge.

344
00:29:05.410 --> 00:29:08.413
prince daemon Targaryen chooses

345
00:29:08.497 --> 00:29:10.999
ser gwayne hightower of oldtown.

346
00:29:11.083 --> 00:29:13.794
eldest son of the hand of the king.

347
00:29:26.556 --> 00:29:28.976
Five dragons on daemon.

348
00:29:49.705 --> 00:29:51.415
Ha!

349
00:30:42.090 --> 00:30:45.093
- Nicely done. uncle.
- Thank you. Princess.

350
00:30:46.303 --> 00:30:50.015
Now. I'm fairly certain
I can win these games. lady alicent.

351
00:30:50.098 --> 00:30:53.101
Having your favor
would all but assure it.

352
00:31:07.657 --> 00:31:09.242
Good luck. my prince.

353
00:31:37.354 --> 00:31:39.940
- What's happening?
- The infant is in breech. your grace.

354
00:31:40.023 --> 00:31:42.442
All attempts to turn the babe
have failed.

355
00:31:44.736 --> 00:31:46.656
- Do something for her!
- We've given her as much

356
00:31:46.738 --> 00:31:49.658
milk of the poppy as we can
without risking the child.

357
00:31:49.741 --> 00:31:51.326
Your queen is a strong woman.

358
00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:54.830
She's fighting with all her might.
but it may not be enough.

359
00:31:54.913 --> 00:31:56.206
No!

360
00:31:56.581 --> 00:31:58.208
Aemma.

361
00:31:59.292 --> 00:32:01.354
Aemma. I'm here.

362
00:32:01.378 --> 00:32:02.712
I'm here.

363
00:32:03.797 --> 00:32:05.715
I'm here. It's all right.

364
00:32:05.799 --> 00:32:07.759
- It's all right.
- I can't do this.

365
00:32:07.843 --> 00:32:10.053
You're going to be all right.

366
00:32:10.137 --> 00:32:11.763
You're going to be all right.

367
00:32:17.227 --> 00:32:18.770
Ah!

368
00:32:31.116 --> 00:32:32.701
{933931 -

369
00:32:36.913 --> 00:32:37.914
Kill him!

370
00:32:37.998 --> 00:32:40.542
And the day grows ugly.

371
00:32:44.087 --> 00:32:48.216
I wonder if this is how we should
celebrate the birth of our future king.

372
00:32:48.300 --> 00:32:50.427
- Hmm.
- With wanton violence.

373
00:32:50.510 --> 00:32:52.947
It's been 70 years
since king maegor's end.

374
00:32:52.971 --> 00:32:54.806
These knights are as green
as summer grass.

375
00:32:54.890 --> 00:32:56.600
None have known real war.

376
00:32:57.726 --> 00:32:59.394
Their lords sent them
to the tourney field

377
00:32:59.478 --> 00:33:02.230
with fists full of steel
and balls full of seed.

378
00:33:02.314 --> 00:33:04.399
and we expect them
to act with honor and grace.

379
00:33:05.066 --> 00:33:07.986
It's a marvel that war
didn't break out at first blood.

380
00:33:10.197 --> 00:33:11.656
{933931 -

381
00:33:30.675 --> 00:33:31.801
Mellos.

382
00:33:32.844 --> 00:33:34.054
Your grace.

383
00:33:35.597 --> 00:33:36.806
If you would.

384
00:33:46.733 --> 00:33:48.318
During a difficult birth.

385
00:33:48.401 --> 00:33:52.822
it sometimes becomes necessary
for the father

386
00:33:53.698 --> 00:33:55.700
to make an impossible choice.

387
00:33:56.993 --> 00:33:58.745
Well. speak it.

388
00:33:58.828 --> 00:34:03.083
To sacrifice one or to lose them both.

389
00:34:04.584 --> 00:34:07.671
There is a chance
that we can save the child.

390
00:34:07.754 --> 00:34:09.756
A technique is taught at the citadel.

391
00:34:09.839 --> 00:34:11.758
which involves cutting
directly into the womb

392
00:34:11.841 --> 00:34:13.843
to free the infant.

393
00:34:13.927 --> 00:34:16.763
- But the resulting blood loss...
- Seven hells. mellos.

394
00:34:29.150 --> 00:34:31.278
You can save the child?

395
00:34:31.361 --> 00:34:35.365
We must either act now
or leave it with the gods.

396
00:34:47.043 --> 00:34:50.088
Ser criston Cole will now tilt against

397
00:34:50.171 --> 00:34:54.175
ser daemon Targaryen.
prince of the city!

398
00:36:05.622 --> 00:36:07.624
- Viserys.
- Yes?

399
00:36:09.542 --> 00:36:11.753
They're going to bring the babe out now.

400
00:36:35.527 --> 00:36:36.736
I love you.

401
00:36:41.783 --> 00:36:42.992
Oh!

402
00:36:44.911 --> 00:36:47.163
- What is happening?
- No. it's all right.

403
00:36:47.247 --> 00:36:50.083
What is happening?

404
00:36:50.166 --> 00:36:52.687
- Viserys. what...
- No. it's all right.

405
00:36:52.711 --> 00:36:54.563
- What are you doing?
- They're going to bring the babe out.

406
00:36:54.587 --> 00:36:55.755
How are they...

407
00:36:55.839 --> 00:36:57.382
- It's all right.
- Viserys. please.

408
00:36:57.465 --> 00:36:59.634
- It's all right.
- No. I'm scared.

409
00:36:59.718 --> 00:37:01.320
- Don't be scared.
- What is happening?

410
00:37:01.344 --> 00:37:02.988
Don't be scared.
They're going to bring the babe out.

411
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:05.348
- No.
- It's all right.

412
00:37:05.432 --> 00:37:07.434
They're going to bring the babe out.

413
00:37:08.393 --> 00:37:11.604
No! No! No!

414
00:37:11.688 --> 00:37:15.817
- I'm making the first incision.
- No. no. no!

415
00:37:16.276 --> 00:37:19.237
Viserys. no! Please!

416
00:37:19.320 --> 00:37:21.698
- No. no. no!
- Don't be scared.

417
00:37:45.847 --> 00:37:47.098
Sword!

418
00:37:47.182 --> 00:37:48.433
Prince daemon Targaryen

419
00:37:48.516 --> 00:37:52.187
wishes to continue in a contest of arms!

420
00:39:38.668 --> 00:39:39.668
Ah!

421
00:39:42.422 --> 00:39:43.840
Yield.

422
00:39:45.258 --> 00:39:46.259
Yield.

423
00:40:20.209 --> 00:40:22.045
Gods. He's dornish.

424
00:40:22.754 --> 00:40:25.340
I was hoping to ask
for the Princess' favor.

425
00:40:37.393 --> 00:40:39.854
I wish you luck. ser criston.

426
00:40:39.938 --> 00:40:41.314
Princess.

427
00:40:52.617 --> 00:40:55.036
Congratulations. your grace.

428
00:40:55.662 --> 00:40:57.121
You have a son.

429
00:41:01.167 --> 00:41:02.502
It's a boy?

430
00:41:02.585 --> 00:41:05.004
A new heir. your grace.

431
00:41:10.677 --> 00:41:13.304
Had you and the queen chosen a name?

432
00:41:16.766 --> 00:41:17.976
Baelon.

433
00:42:35.887 --> 00:42:37.889
They're waiting for you.

434
00:43:33.736 --> 00:43:34.904
Dracarys.

435
00:44:14.402 --> 00:44:15.879
- Where's rhaenyra?
- Your grace.

436
00:44:15.903 --> 00:44:19.699
This is the last thing any of us
wish to discuss at this dark hour.

437
00:44:19.782 --> 00:44:22.118
but I consider the matter urgent.

438
00:44:22.201 --> 00:44:23.202
What matter?

439
00:44:24.579 --> 00:44:26.164
That of your succession.

440
00:44:26.831 --> 00:44:30.376
These recent tragedies
have left you without an obvious heir.

441
00:44:30.459 --> 00:44:32.253
The king has an heir. my lord hand.

442
00:44:32.336 --> 00:44:34.797
Despite how difficult
this time is. your grace.

443
00:44:34.881 --> 00:44:38.009
I feel it important
the succession be firmly in place

444
00:44:38.092 --> 00:44:39.552
for the stability of the realm.

445
00:44:39.635 --> 00:44:41.804
The succession is already set

446
00:44:41.888 --> 00:44:43.389
by precedent and by law.

447
00:44:43.472 --> 00:44:45.099
Shall we say his name?

448
00:44:47.643 --> 00:44:49.187
Daemon Targaryen.

449
00:44:49.270 --> 00:44:52.190
If daemon were to remain
the uncontested heir.

450
00:44:52.273 --> 00:44:54.775
it could destabilize the realm.

451
00:44:54.859 --> 00:44:56.777
The realm? Or this council?

452
00:44:56.861 --> 00:44:59.655
No one here can know
what daemon would do were he king.

453
00:44:59.739 --> 00:45:02.366
but no one can doubt his ambition.

454
00:45:02.450 --> 00:45:05.119
Look at what he did
with the gold cloaks.

455
00:45:05.203 --> 00:45:07.246
The city watch is fiercely loyal to him.

456
00:45:07.330 --> 00:45:11.125
- An army 2.000 strong.
- An army you gave him. Otto.

457
00:45:11.209 --> 00:45:15.171
I named daemon master of laws.
but you said he was a tyrant.

458
00:45:15.254 --> 00:45:17.715
As master of coin.
you said he was a spendthrift

459
00:45:17.798 --> 00:45:19.300
that would beggar the realm.

460
00:45:19.383 --> 00:45:21.594
Putting daemon in command
of the city watch

461
00:45:21.677 --> 00:45:23.137
was your solution!

462
00:45:23.221 --> 00:45:25.223
A half-measure. your grace.

463
00:45:25.306 --> 00:45:28.309
The truth is. daemon should be
far away from this court.

464
00:45:28.392 --> 00:45:29.560
Daemon is my brother.

465
00:45:30.603 --> 00:45:31.812
My blood.

466
00:45:32.772 --> 00:45:34.732
And he will have his place at my court.

467
00:45:34.815 --> 00:45:36.877
Let him keep his place
at court. your grace.

468
00:45:36.901 --> 00:45:41.072
but if the gods should visit
some further tragedy on you.

469
00:45:41.155 --> 00:45:44.367
- either by design or by accident.
- "Design"?

470
00:45:44.909 --> 00:45:46.285
What are you saying?

471
00:45:46.369 --> 00:45:48.704
My brother would murder me.
take my crown?

472
00:45:50.414 --> 00:45:51.415
Are you?

473
00:45:53.292 --> 00:45:54.293
Please.

474
00:45:55.461 --> 00:45:59.131
Daemon has ambition. yes.
but not for the throne.

475
00:45:59.215 --> 00:46:00.925
He lacks the Patience for it.

476
00:46:01.008 --> 00:46:02.510
The gods have yet to make a man

477
00:46:02.593 --> 00:46:06.138
who lacks the Patience
for absolute power. your grace.

478
00:46:06.222 --> 00:46:10.226
Under such circumstances.
it would not be an aberration

479
00:46:10.309 --> 00:46:12.895
for the king to name a successor.

480
00:46:12.979 --> 00:46:14.689
Well. who else would have a claim?

481
00:46:21.320 --> 00:46:23.489
The king's firstborn child.

482
00:46:23.572 --> 00:46:25.741
Rhaenyra? A girl?

483
00:46:27.451 --> 00:46:29.412
No queen has ever sat the iron throne.

484
00:46:29.495 --> 00:46:31.622
That is only by tradition
and precedent. lord strong.

485
00:46:31.706 --> 00:46:33.916
If order and stability
so concerns this council.

486
00:46:34.000 --> 00:46:37.837
then perhaps we shouldn't break
100 years of it by naming a girl heir.

487
00:46:37.920 --> 00:46:41.674
Daemon would be a second maegor.
or worse.

488
00:46:41.757 --> 00:46:43.759
He is impulsive and violent.

489
00:46:44.468 --> 00:46:46.345
It is the duty of this council

490
00:46:46.429 --> 00:46:49.432
to protect the king
and the realm from him.

491
00:46:50.808 --> 00:46:53.185
I'm sorry. your grace.
but that is the truth as I see it.

492
00:46:53.269 --> 00:46:54.812
and I know that others here agree.

493
00:46:54.895 --> 00:46:58.858
I will not be made to choose
between my brother and my daughter.

494
00:46:58.941 --> 00:47:00.776
You wouldn't have to.
your grace.

495
00:47:00.860 --> 00:47:02.903
There are others who would have a claim.

496
00:47:02.987 --> 00:47:05.031
Such as your wife. lord corlys?

497
00:47:05.114 --> 00:47:07.354
- "The queen who never was"?
- Rhaenys was the only child

498
00:47:07.408 --> 00:47:08.576
of jaehaerys' eldest son.

499
00:47:08.659 --> 00:47:10.661
She had a strong claim
at the great council.

500
00:47:10.745 --> 00:47:12.705
and she already has a male heir.

501
00:47:12.788 --> 00:47:15.207
Just moments ago.
you announced your support for daemon!

502
00:47:15.291 --> 00:47:17.311
If we cannot agree on an heir.
then how can we expect...

503
00:47:17.335 --> 00:47:18.753
My wife and son are dead!

504
00:47:20.963 --> 00:47:25.509
I will not sit here and suffer crows
that come to feast on their corpses!

505
00:47:59.377 --> 00:48:01.003
Send a raven to oldtown.

506
00:48:01.462 --> 00:48:02.797
Straight away.

507
00:48:05.549 --> 00:48:06.634
My lady.

508
00:48:17.311 --> 00:48:18.354
My darling.

509
00:48:27.905 --> 00:48:29.031
How's rhaenyra?

510
00:48:32.118 --> 00:48:33.285
She lost her mother.

511
00:48:35.329 --> 00:48:37.456
The queen was well-loved by all.

512
00:48:40.042 --> 00:48:43.254
I found myself thinking
of your own mother today.

513
00:48:49.844 --> 00:48:52.471
- How is his grace?
- Very low.

514
00:48:53.931 --> 00:48:55.808
Which is why I sent for you.

515
00:49:01.105 --> 00:49:02.690
I thought you might go to him.

516
00:49:03.858 --> 00:49:04.942
offer him comfort.

517
00:49:07.987 --> 00:49:09.155
In his chambers?

518
00:49:15.870 --> 00:49:17.371
I wouldn't know what to say.

519
00:49:18.414 --> 00:49:19.540
Stop that.

520
00:49:21.584 --> 00:49:23.127
He'll be glad of a visitor.

521
00:49:31.760 --> 00:49:33.846
You might wear
one of your mother's dresses.

522
00:50:10.925 --> 00:50:13.552
The lady alicent hightower. your grace.

523
00:50:19.266 --> 00:50:20.976
What is it. alicent?

524
00:50:21.060 --> 00:50:23.187
I thought I might come
and look in on you. your grace.

525
00:50:25.523 --> 00:50:26.941
I brought a book.

526
00:50:29.235 --> 00:50:30.778
That's very kind. thank you.

527
00:50:36.283 --> 00:50:37.785
It's a favorite of mine.

528
00:50:38.702 --> 00:50:41.330
I do know how passionate
you are for the histories.

529
00:50:42.623 --> 00:50:44.625
Yes. I am.

530
00:51:02.268 --> 00:51:03.310
When my mother died.

531
00:51:05.271 --> 00:51:07.022
people only ever spoke to me in riddles.

532
00:51:09.400 --> 00:51:11.610
All I wanted was for someone
to say that they were sorry

533
00:51:11.694 --> 00:51:12.736
for what happened to me.

534
00:51:17.449 --> 00:51:18.784
I'm very sorry. your grace.

535
00:52:07.249 --> 00:52:08.250
Thank you.

536
00:52:10.419 --> 00:52:12.796
The king's sole heir once again.

537
00:52:14.673 --> 00:52:17.468
Might we drink to our future?

538
00:52:18.969 --> 00:52:20.679
Quiet!

539
00:52:20.763 --> 00:52:23.390
Your prince will speak!

540
00:52:26.477 --> 00:52:28.479
Shence!

541
00:52:34.360 --> 00:52:36.403
Before we begin. your grace.

542
00:52:36.487 --> 00:52:40.491
I have a report
I feel compelled to share.

543
00:52:42.576 --> 00:52:43.786
Last night.

544
00:52:44.620 --> 00:52:47.289
prince daemon bought out
one of the pleasure houses

545
00:52:47.373 --> 00:52:48.999
on the street of silk.

546
00:52:50.000 --> 00:52:53.253
to entertain officers of the city watch

547
00:52:53.337 --> 00:52:54.963
and other friends of his.

548
00:52:58.676 --> 00:53:00.844
King and council
have long rued my position

549
00:53:00.928 --> 00:53:03.055
as next in line for the throne.

550
00:53:04.390 --> 00:53:06.934
But dream and pray
as they all might.

551
00:53:07.017 --> 00:53:10.604
it seems I'm not so easily replaced.

552
00:53:12.231 --> 00:53:14.983
The gods give
just as the gods take away.

553
00:53:15.067 --> 00:53:16.944
He toasted prince baelon.

554
00:53:17.027 --> 00:53:18.195
To the king's son.

555
00:53:19.238 --> 00:53:20.656
Styling him

556
00:53:21.990 --> 00:53:24.576
"the heir for a day."

557
00:53:31.417 --> 00:53:35.337
I corroborated this report
with three separate witnesses.

558
00:53:35.421 --> 00:53:39.258
The evening was.
by all accounts. a celebration.

559
00:53:41.802 --> 00:53:44.304
You cut the image
of the conqueror. brother.

560
00:53:46.265 --> 00:53:47.558
Did you say it?

561
00:53:49.852 --> 00:53:51.186
I don't know what you mean.

562
00:53:51.270 --> 00:53:52.747
You will address me
as "your grace."

563
00:53:52.771 --> 00:53:56.108
or I will have my kingsguard
cut out your tongue.

564
00:53:59.611 --> 00:54:04.032
"The heir for a day." Did you say it?

565
00:54:13.500 --> 00:54:16.545
We must all mourn
in our own way. your grace.

566
00:54:17.963 --> 00:54:21.341
My family has just been destroyed.

567
00:54:22.426 --> 00:54:25.596
But instead of being
by my side. or rhaenyra's.

568
00:54:25.679 --> 00:54:28.390
you chose to celebrate your own rise!

569
00:54:28.474 --> 00:54:31.185
Laughing with your whores
and your iickspittles!

570
00:54:33.812 --> 00:54:36.899
You have no allies at court but me!

571
00:54:36.982 --> 00:54:39.693
I have only ever defended you!

572
00:54:39.777 --> 00:54:42.196
Yet everything I've given you.
you've thrown back in my face.

573
00:54:42.279 --> 00:54:44.114
You've only ever tried to send me away.

574
00:54:44.198 --> 00:54:46.909
To the vale. to the city watch.

575
00:54:46.992 --> 00:54:48.952
anywhere but by your side.

576
00:54:49.036 --> 00:54:51.079
Ten years you've been king.

577
00:54:51.163 --> 00:54:54.291
and yet not once have you
asked me to be your hand!

578
00:54:54.374 --> 00:54:57.461
- Why would I do that?
- Because I'm your brother.

579
00:54:58.504 --> 00:55:00.464
And the blood of the dragon runs thick.

580
00:55:00.547 --> 00:55:02.549
Then why do you cut me so deeply?

581
00:55:02.633 --> 00:55:05.636
I've only ever spoken the truth.
I see Otto hightower for what he is.

582
00:55:06.720 --> 00:55:08.198
An unwavering and loyal hand?

583
00:55:08.222 --> 00:55:09.222
A cunt.

584
00:55:10.724 --> 00:55:12.726
A second son
who stands to inherit nothing

585
00:55:12.810 --> 00:55:14.228
he doesn't seize for himself.

586
00:55:14.311 --> 00:55:16.396
Otto hightower is a more honorable man

587
00:55:16.480 --> 00:55:18.607
- than you could ever be.
- He doesn't protect you.

588
00:55:18.690 --> 00:55:20.651
- I would.
- From what?

589
00:55:20.734 --> 00:55:21.944
Yourself.

590
00:55:25.656 --> 00:55:28.408
You're weak. viserys.

591
00:55:30.953 --> 00:55:32.454
And that council of leeches knows it.

592
00:55:32.538 --> 00:55:34.540
They all prey on you for their own ends.

593
00:55:39.461 --> 00:55:41.547
I have decided to name a new heir.

594
00:55:41.630 --> 00:55:44.258
- I'm your heir.
- Not anymore.

595
00:55:45.676 --> 00:55:49.304
You are to return to runestone
and your lady wife at once.

596
00:55:49.388 --> 00:55:51.473
and you are to do so without quarrel

597
00:55:52.558 --> 00:55:54.560
by order of your king.

598
00:56:09.491 --> 00:56:10.909
Your grace.

599
00:57:10.427 --> 00:57:11.637
Father.

600
00:57:15.891 --> 00:57:17.726
Balerion was the last living creature

601
00:57:17.809 --> 00:57:20.103
to have seen old valyria
before the doom.

602
00:57:23.106 --> 00:57:25.192
Its greatness and its flaws.

603
00:57:25.734 --> 00:57:28.278
When you look at the dragons.
what do you see?

604
00:57:28.362 --> 00:57:29.404
What?

605
00:57:29.488 --> 00:57:32.658
You haven't spoken a word to me
since mother's funeral.

606
00:57:32.741 --> 00:57:35.160
- and now you send your kingsguard down.
- Answer me.

607
00:57:38.205 --> 00:57:39.206
It's important.

608
00:57:40.290 --> 00:57:41.708
What do you see?

609
00:57:49.549 --> 00:57:52.177
- I suppose I see us.
- Tell me.

610
00:57:53.261 --> 00:57:57.140
Everyone says targaryens
are closer to gods than to men.

611
00:57:57.224 --> 00:57:59.476
but they say that
because of our dragons.

612
00:58:01.395 --> 00:58:03.981
Without them.
we're just like everyone else.

613
00:58:06.566 --> 00:58:09.736
The idea that we control the dragons

614
00:58:10.654 --> 00:58:12.280
is an illusion.

615
00:58:13.991 --> 00:58:16.994
They're a power man should
never have trifled with.

616
00:58:18.453 --> 00:58:20.831
One that brought valyria its doom.

617
00:58:20.914 --> 00:58:24.501
If we don't mind our own histories.
it will do the same to us.

618
00:58:25.043 --> 00:58:27.254
Targaryen must understand
this to be king

619
00:58:29.047 --> 00:58:30.048
or queen.

620
00:58:34.469 --> 00:58:36.096
I'm sorry. rhaenyra.

621
00:58:37.055 --> 00:58:40.017
I have wasted the years
since you were born

622
00:58:40.100 --> 00:58:41.226
wanting for a son.

623
00:58:53.697 --> 00:58:55.782
You are the very best of your mother.

624
00:58:58.910 --> 00:59:01.079
And I believe it. I know she did.

625
00:59:01.163 --> 00:59:03.498
that you could be a great ruling queen.

626
00:59:03.582 --> 00:59:05.292
Daemon is your heir.

627
00:59:06.918 --> 00:59:09.629
Daemon was not made
to wear the crown.

628
00:59:10.130 --> 00:59:11.715
But I believe that you were.

629
00:59:12.799 --> 00:59:15.761
Corlys of house velaryon.

630
00:59:15.844 --> 00:59:19.931
lord of the tides
and master of driftmark.

631
00:59:20.015 --> 00:59:22.517
I. corlys velaryon.

632
00:59:23.226 --> 00:59:26.396
lord of the tides
and master of driftmark.

633
00:59:26.480 --> 00:59:28.565
promise to be faithful to king viserys

634
00:59:28.648 --> 00:59:31.485
and his named heir.
the Princess rhaenyra.

635
00:59:31.568 --> 00:59:32.778
I pledge fealty to them

636
00:59:33.904 --> 00:59:35.822
and shall defend them
against all enemies

637
00:59:35.906 --> 00:59:38.533
in good faith and without deceit.

638
00:59:42.871 --> 00:59:45.874
I swear this
by the old gods and the new.

639
00:59:48.585 --> 00:59:50.796
This is no trivial gesture.
rhaenyra.

640
00:59:51.296 --> 00:59:53.715
A dragon's saddle is one thing.

641
00:59:53.799 --> 00:59:56.718
but the iron throne is the most
dangerous seat in the realm.

642
00:59:57.594 --> 00:59:59.554
I. lord hobert hightower.

643
00:59:59.638 --> 01:00:01.973
beacon of the south.
defender of the citadel.

644
01:00:02.057 --> 01:00:03.600
and voice of oldtown.

645
01:00:03.683 --> 01:00:05.977
promise to be faithful to king viserys

646
01:00:06.061 --> 01:00:09.648
and his named heir.
the Princess rhaenyra.

647
01:00:12.359 --> 01:00:13.944
I pledge fealty to them

648
01:00:14.027 --> 01:00:15.946
and shall defend them
against all enemies

649
01:00:16.029 --> 01:00:18.865
in good faith and without deceit.

650
01:00:19.491 --> 01:00:22.619
I swear this
by the old gods and the new.

651
01:00:29.501 --> 01:00:30.919
Give me your hand.

652
01:00:45.517 --> 01:00:47.435
I. boremund Baratheon.

653
01:00:48.603 --> 01:00:51.815
promise to be faithful to king viserys.

654
01:00:53.942 --> 01:00:56.945
There's something else
that I need to tell you.

655
01:00:57.696 --> 01:00:59.865
It might be difficult
for you to understand.

656
01:00:59.948 --> 01:01:01.199
but you must hear it.

657
01:01:02.492 --> 01:01:03.952
Our histories.

658
01:01:04.035 --> 01:01:07.164
they tell us that aegon looked across
the Blackwater from dragonstone.

659
01:01:07.247 --> 01:01:09.875
saw a rich land ripe for the capture.

660
01:01:11.209 --> 01:01:14.212
But ambition alone is not
what drove him to conquest.

661
01:01:15.130 --> 01:01:16.423
It was a dream.

662
01:01:17.174 --> 01:01:19.551
And just as daenys foresaw
the end of valyria.

663
01:01:19.634 --> 01:01:22.262
aegon foresaw
the end of the world of men.

664
01:01:23.138 --> 01:01:25.974
'Tis to begin with a terrible winter

665
01:01:26.057 --> 01:01:28.310
gusting out of the distant north.

666
01:01:28.393 --> 01:01:30.270
I. rickon stark.

667
01:01:30.353 --> 01:01:31.605
lord of winterfell...

668
01:01:31.688 --> 01:01:35.108
Aegon saw absolute darkness
riding on those winds.

669
01:01:35.192 --> 01:01:38.361
And whatever dwells within
will destroy the world of the living.

670
01:01:39.446 --> 01:01:41.448
When this great winter comes. rhaenyra.

671
01:01:42.741 --> 01:01:45.368
all of Westeros must stand against it.

672
01:01:45.452 --> 01:01:46.971
And if the world of men is to survive.

673
01:01:46.995 --> 01:01:49.956
a Targaryen must be seated
on the iron throne.

674
01:01:50.040 --> 01:01:53.126
A king or queen.
strong enough to unite the realm

675
01:01:53.210 --> 01:01:55.795
against the cold and the dark.

676
01:01:58.006 --> 01:02:00.800
Aegon called his dream
"the song of ice and fire."

677
01:02:03.762 --> 01:02:04.930
This secret.

678
01:02:06.014 --> 01:02:08.975
it's been passed from king to heir
since aegon's time.

679
01:02:10.477 --> 01:02:12.687
Now you must promise to carry it

680
01:02:13.230 --> 01:02:14.314
and protect it.

681
01:02:17.817 --> 01:02:19.945
Promise me this. rhaenyra.

682
01:02:24.074 --> 01:02:25.283
Promise me.

683
01:02:31.331 --> 01:02:36.461
I. viserys Targaryen.
first of his name...

684
01:02:38.129 --> 01:02:40.507
King of the andals.
and the rhoynar.

685
01:02:40.590 --> 01:02:42.759
and the first men.

686
01:02:42.842 --> 01:02:45.095
lord of the seven kingdoms.

687
01:02:45.178 --> 01:02:47.180
and protector of the realm.

688
01:02:47.973 --> 01:02:49.516
do hereby name

689
01:02:50.225 --> 01:02:52.269
rhaenyra Targaryen.

690
01:02:52.352 --> 01:02:54.604
Princess of dragonstone

691
01:02:54.688 --> 01:02:56.940
and heir to the iron throne.
